    section.section--different
        .wrap--content

            h1.
                Binge eating disorder (!{BED}) is different from bulimia nervosa

    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h2.
                !{BED} is not associated with compensatory behaviors like purging or excessive exercise, or with dietary restriction, though frequent dieting may be reported#[sup 1]

    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h1.
                !{BED} is different from overeating

    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h2.
                While overeating is a challenge for many Americans, recurrent binge eating is much less common, far more severe, and is associated with significant physical and psychological problems#[sup 2]

    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h1.
                !{BED} is different from obesity

    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h2.
                Although !{BED} can be associated with increased weight, it occurs in normal-weight, overweight, and obese adults#[sup 3]


    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h1.
                The majority of adults with !{BED} are not obese*#[sup 3]:


