    section.section--
        .wrap--content

            h1.
                Compared with weight-matched obese adults without !{BED}, obese adults with !{BED} eat more calories in studies of how people eat and show#[sup 1]:

            ul.square
                li.
                    More functional impairment
                li.
                    Greater self-reported distress
                li.
                    Impaired quality of life
                li.
                    More coexisting psychiatric conditions

            .box

                h2.
                    At rates similar to those with bulimia and anorexia, adults with !{BED} may have coexisting psychiatric and physical conditions like bipolar disorders, depressive disorders, anxiety disorders, substance use disorders, and obesity#[sup 1]

                h4.
                    Lifetime psychiatric comorbidity associated with !{BED}*#[sup 3]


